Privacy Policy
General
This Privacy Policy describes Deferit, Inc.’s and any of our affiliates (collectively, “Deferit,” “we”, “us”, or “our”) practices and the privacy rights of users of Deferit Services (“you”) regarding our collection, use, storage, sharing and protection of your personal information. It applies to the Deferit website and all related sites, applications, services and tools, including the Deferit app, regardless of how you access or use them. We may offer you the ability to connect with Deferit Services using a mobile device, either through a mobile application or via a mobile optimized website. The provisions of this Privacy Policy apply to all such mobile access and use of mobile devices.
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By accessing and using this website or any other Deferit Services, you confirm that you have read and understand this Privacy Policy in its entirety. You understand and acknowledge that we reserve the right to change or amend this Privacy Policy at any time. When we do this, the revised Privacy Policy will be effective from the time we post it.  We may also highlight any material changes to our Privacy Policy that may impact you by notifying you via email or otherwise.
If you do not agree to this Privacy Policy in its entirety, you must refrain from using the Deferit Services. This Privacy Policy applies US law and is intended to govern the use of Deferit Services by our users (including, without limitation those who use the Deferit Services in the course of their trade or business) in the United States.
Throughout this Privacy Policy, unless otherwise stated, we use the term “personal information” to describe information that can be associated with a specific person and can be used to identify that person. We do not consider personal information to include information that has been made anonymous so that it does not identify a specific user.
Collection of Personal Information
We collect and use the personal information that you give us to provide our products and services, and for the purposes which are reasonably necessary for our business activities to function or if required by law.
Information we learn from use
When you use Deferit Services, we may collect information sent to us by your computer, mobile phone or other access device. The information sent to us may include, but is not limited to, the following: data about the pages you access, computer IP address, device ID or unique identifier, device type, geo-location information, computer and connection information, mobile network information, statistics on page views, traffic to and from the sites, referral URL, ad data, and standard web log data and other information. We also collect anonymous information through our use of cookies and web beacons.
When you download or use our mobile applications, or access one of our mobile optimized sites, we may receive information about your location and your mobile device, including a unique identifier for your device. We may use this information to provide you with location-based services, such as advertising, search results, and other personalized content. Most mobile devices allow you to control or disable location services in the device’s setting’s menu. If you have questions about how to disable your device’s location services, we recommend you contact your mobile service carrier or the manufacturer of your particular device.
We may also collect information from or about you other than through your use of the Deferit Services, such as through your contact with us, including our customer support team, your results when you respond to a survey, your interactions with members of the Deferit corporate family or other companies (subject to their privacy policies and applicable law), and from other accounts we have reason to believe you control (whether in part or in whole). Additionally, for quality and training purposes or for its own protection, Deferit may monitor or record its telephone conversations with you or anyone acting on your behalf, subject to applicable law. By communicating with Deferit, unless otherwise provided by applicable law, you acknowledge that your communication may be overheard, monitored, or recorded without further notice or warning.
Information we collect when using our service
We may collect and store any information you provide us when you use Deferit Services, including when you add information on a web form, add or update your account information, participate in community discussions, chats, or dispute resolutions, or when you otherwise correspond with us regarding Deferit Services.
When you use Deferit Services, we also may collect information about your transactions and your activities, such as records of services considered, as well as purchasing or consuming histories or tendencies. In addition, if you open a Deferit account or use Deferit Services, we may collect the following types of information:
Contact and personal information: such as your name, address, phone number, email and other similar information.
Financial information: such as information about your current employer and your employment history and the full bank account numbers and/or credit card numbers that you linked to your Deferit account or give us when you use Deferit Services.
Detailed personal information: such as your date of birth, Social Security Number or driver’s license number or information contained in other identification documents.
Biometric information: such as information about your physiological, biological and behavioral characteristics.
Information from third parties: such as credit bureaus and identity verification services with whom we have contractual relationships.
You may also choose to provide us with access to certain personal information stored by third parties such as social media sites (e.g., Facebook and Twitter). The information we may receive varies by site and is controlled by that site.
By associating an account managed by a third party with your Deferit account and authorizing Deferit to have access to this information, you agree that Deferit may collect, store and use this information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
